<title>UK: Nelson Hurst pre-tax, pre-excep profit up.</title>
<headline>Nelson Hurst pre-tax, pre-excep profit up.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-09-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Half year to June 30</p>
<p>			   (million stg unless stated)</p>
<p> Shr (pence)		 7.9		    vs 7.6</p>
<p> Shr (pence) post excep  7.9		    vs 9.1</p>
<p> Dividend (pence)	  2.85		   vs 2.60</p>
<p> Pretax			6.12		   vs 6.41</p>
<p> Pretax, pre-exceps	6.12		   vs 5.43</p>
<p> Turnover		    27.04		  vs 23.86</p>
<p> Operating Profit	  6.17		   vs 5.48</p>
<p> Investment income	 1.94		   vs 2.02</p>
<p> Other income		0.30		   vs 0.04 loss</p>
<p> Total revenue	     29.28		  vs 25.83</p>
<p> Tax			   1.99		   vs 2.13</p>
<p> Net taxed		   4.13		   vs 4.25</p>
<p> Attributable		3.59		   vs 4.12</p>
<p> Pay date		    October 9</p>
<p> Div registration date   September 24</p>
<p> Ex-div date		 September 16</p>
<p>NOTE - Insurance broker Nelson Hurst Plc said business conditions remain difficult with pressure on margins but added it was confident in its ability to turn business opportunities to its advantage even during difficult times. -- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7717.</p>
</text>
